%N A393862 O.g.f. A(x) satisfies: [x^n] exp( n^6*x - n^2*A(x) ) = 0 for n >= 1.
%H A393862 Paul D. Hanna, <a href="/A393862/b393862.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..201</a>
%e A393862 O.g.f.: A(x) = x + 450*x^2 + 6588000*x^3 + 690998580000*x^4 + 296099442634500000*x^5 + 381339445618842253200000*x^6 + ...
%e A393862 ILLUSTRATION OF DEFINITION.
%e A393862 The table of coefficients of x^k/k! in exp( n^6*x - n^2*A(x) ) begins
%e A393862   n = 1: [1,     0,      -900,     -39528000, ...];
%e A393862   n = 2: [1,    60,         0,    -158544000, ...];
%e A393862   n = 3: [1,   720,    510300,             0, ...];
%e A393862   n = 4: [1,  4080,  16632000,   67108608000, 0, ...];
%e A393862   n = 5: [1, 15600, 243337500, 3794374800000, 58714974690750000, 0, ...]; ...
%e A393862 in which a diagonal, the coefficient of x^n in row n, is all zeros.
%e A393862 RELATED SERIES.
%e A393862 exp(A(x)) = 1 + x + 901*x^2/2! + 39530701*x^3/3! + 16584126467401*x^4/4! + 35532016392129039001*x^5/5! + 274564614276924192666823501*x^6/6! + ...
%e A393862 where [x^n] exp(n^6*x) / exp(A(x))^(n^2) = 0 for n >= 1.
%o A393862 (PARI) {a(n,p=6,q=2) = my(A=[0], m); for(i=1, n+1, m=#A; A=concat(A, 0); A[m+1] = Vec( exp(m^p*x - m^q*Ser(A)) )[m+1]/(m^q) ); polcoef( Ser(A), n)}
%o A393862 for(n=1, 15, print1(a(n,6,2), ", "))
%Y A393862 Below, sequences with the parameters (p,q) indicated have an o.g.f. F(x) satisfying [x^n] exp( n^p*x - n^q*F(x) ) = 0 for n >= 1.
